<HEADLINE> News Analysis: From Emancipation of Mind to Unified Thinking (1) (By Zhou Shuchun) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The warm response to Jiang
Zemin's report at the on-going Party Congress has proven that the
2000-plus delegates have reached a consensus on a series of key
issues.
</P>
<P>
Reaching unified thinking through emancipation of the mind has
been an outstanding characteristic of the current 15th National
Congress of the Communist Party of China, which opened on
September 12.
</P>
<P>
Jiang Zemin gave a profound exposition of a wide-range of
issues concerning different aspects of reform and opening-up as
well as the socialist modernization drive. The greatest responses
have come from the proposal to write down Deng Xiaoping Theory
into the Party Constitution as the Party's guiding ideology, the
affirmation to the primary stage of socialism and the
breakthroughs in understanding the meaning of public ownership.
</P>
<P>
The series of important proposals put forward by Jiang Zemin at
the congress on behalf of the 14th Communist Party Central
Committee have been recognized by delegates who are working as
senior officials at the central government level, celebrities
engaged in theoretical rearch, scientists, teachers, artists,
workers, farmers, army officers and rank-and-file.
</P>
<P>
Their consensus has constituted the most important achievement
of the congress, observers say.
</P>
<P>
The proposal to amend the CPC Constitution is also a key step
to holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
As a matter of fact, China's reform and opening-up has been
guided by the theory from the very beginning, and the 14th CPC
Central Committee with Jiang Zemin at the core has affirmed the
guiding position of Deng Xiaoping Theory in the whole Party.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0007 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: From Emancipation of Mind to Unified Thinking (2) (By Zhou Shuchun) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The congress delegates pointed out that the third generation of
the CPC Central Committee leadership has clearly inscribed Deng
Xiaoping Theory on the Party flag not long after Deng Xiaoping
passed away. The significance and impact of this move is "fairly
profound," "far-reaching" and "immeasurab," the delegates said.
</P>
<P>
It is true that the Party members, cadres and the general
public have seen the hopes from the results of reform and
opening-up in the past 20 years. That's also something to be
expected that they share the view in the current Party Congress to
hold high the banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
Owing to the above factors, they unanimously hailed the third
generation of collective leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core
as "staunch and firm successor of Deng Xiaoping Theory."
</P>
<P>
The definition of the "primary stage of socialism" was put
forward in the 13th Party congress ten years ago. However,
delegates held that the affirmation to the definition in the
current congress has enriched the theory. The congress has, for
the first time, made a systematic exposition of the basic guiding
principle of the primary stage of socialism, which is of important
immediate significance.
</P>
<P>
The reasons are clear: there are still some dubious or wrong
understanding of the current state situation. Meanwhile, with
reform heading to the critical period, contradiction of various
kinds are becoming more obvious and must be properly handled
according to China's reality.
</P>
<P>
That's why the delegates pointed out that the significance of
the exposition of the primary stage of socialism is not only the
perfection in theory but the guidance in practice.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0008 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: From Emancipation of Mind to Unified Thinking (3) (By Zhou Shuchun) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
The report pointed out China is currently in the primary stage
of socialism and will remain in the stage for a long time to come.
</P>
<P>
More importantly, the report called for top priority to
concentrating on the development of productive forces, a historic
process that will last at least a century.
</P>
<P>
One of the fundamental reasons why major errors occurred prior
to the country's reforms and opening-up lay in the fact that some
tasks and policies set forth at that time had overstepped the
primary stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
Once thorough agreement has been reached throughout the Party
and the country in this regard, it is highly likely that the basic
line of the Party will be upheld for another century, literally as
what the Party has anticipated.
</P>
<P>
The delegates also shared the view that the congress has
offered a definite, clear and creative explanation of the issue of
public ownership, one that touches upon the most sensitive part of
the on-going economic restructuring in the country.
</P>
<P>
As far as delegates from the economic and theoretical circles
are concerned, the theoretical breakthrough concerning ownership
has pointed a way out for the economic restructuring, especially
the reform of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
Though the realization of diverse forms of public owership may
give rise to a drop in the proportion of the state sector to the
entire economy, the delegates agreed that it will not change the
socialist nature of China.
</P>
<P>
As the delegates indicated, the exposition of these important
issues in the report embodies the spirit of "emancipating the mind
and seeking truth from facts."
</P>
<P>
This principle should continue to receive utmost attention, the
delegates noted. Whatever undertakings conducive to reforms,
development and stability of the country should be bravely tried,
they said.
</P>
<P>
For delegates from regions where reforms began ahead of other
places, the theoretical breakthrough concerning ownership has been
no less a blessing.
</P>
<P>
Besides, delegates have shown universal approval of the major
parts of the report, including those on building a country ruled
by law, developing socialist democracy, building socialist culture
with Chinese characteristics, promoting peaceful unification of
the motherland, and cutting the size of the armed forces by
500,000.
</P>
<P>
Currently, the delegates are considering how to translate the
common understanding reached at the congress into unified will and
action throughout the Party and the whole country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
