<HEADLINE> Non-Communist Parties Hail CPC National Congress (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The central committees of all
non-communist parties in China and the All-China Federation of
Industry and Commerce have sent letters of congratulations on
the convening of the 15th National Congress of the Communist
Party of China (CPC), which opened here last Friday.
</P>
<P>
A letter of congratulations from the Central Committee of the
Revolutionary Committee of the Chinese Kuomintang said the CPC
congress is a new milestone in the history of China for holding
high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory for an all-round
advancement of the cause of building socialism with Chinese
characteristics to the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
Facts have proved that Deng's theory is a guideline for all
trades, the theoretical foundation for formulating line,
principles and policies and the spiritual support of the Chinese
nation to revitalize the country, it said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC Central Committee with Jiang Zemin as the core is a
staunch collective leadership which enjoys the love and trust of
the people of all nationalities in China, it added.
</P>
<P>
The China Democratic League said in its letter of
congratulations that the CPC congress is bound to draw up a
blueprint for China's reforms and opening-up and lead the Chinese
people to push forward the great cause of building socialism with
Chinese characteristics into the 21st century.
</P>
<P>
To achieve this objective, it will continue to adhere and
improve the political consultative system of multi-party
cooperation under the leadership of the CPC and make fresh
contributions to the prosperity and reunification of China, it
said.
</P>
<P>
The CPC is worthy of the core of leadership of the Chinese
revolution and construction. Deng Xiaoping Theory is the only
correct theory guiding the Chinese people to achieving
modernization in the course of reforms and opening-up, it said.
</P>
<P>
The basic line for the primary stage of socialism is the
guarantee for the healthy development of the cause of socialism,
it added.
</P>
</TEXT>
