<HEADLINE> Netherlands Budgets Billion Dollars for Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>

<P>
 Protection
</P>
<P>
BRUSSELS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A total of 1.5 billion
guilders (some 940 million U.S. dollars) has been budgeted by the
Dutch government for its soil decontamination works in the period
from 1998 to 2010, it was learned here today.
</P>
<P>
The government is providing 185 million guilders (some 116
million dollars) in support of a large-scale program for the
introduction of cleaner trucks and buses in the period from 1998
to 2004, according to Netherlands News Monitor, a selected list of
government press releases.
</P>
<P>
The press release also said that the sum of 750 million guilders
(469 million dollars) earmarked last year for its CO2 (carbon
dioxide) policy up to the end of 2009 was being doubled.
</P>
<P>
This autumn the government will publish the Third National
Environmental Policy Plan, which will focus primarily on the problem
of the threat of climate change, soil clean-up, the drying-out of
the countryside, noise pollution and the protection of
bio-diversity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
