<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French PM Wishes Good Result from Albright Mideast Tour </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- French Prime Minister Lionel
Jospin said today that he wishes "positive consequences" from
the tour made last week by United States Secretary of State
Madeleine Albright in the Mideast.
</P>
<P>
He made the statement during a dinner with former Israeli Prime
Minister Shimon Peres, who was on a visit here.
</P>
<P>
Peres said that he was not optimistic about the perspective of
the Mideast peace process in a short term period, but he was
optimistic for a long-term period.
</P>
<P>
He pointed out that Arabs and Israelis had fought five wars in
the past, but neither side wants to have a sixth.
</P>
<P>
He said that Israel won the five wars militarily but not
politically, while the Arabs lost the wars both militarily and
politically.
</P>
<P>
"Another war will not solve any problem... There should be an
intervention of reality and real choices," he said.
</P>
<P>
On the severe criticism launched last week by French Foreign
Minister Hubert Vedrine on Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin
Netanyahu, Peres said that the foreign minister could "also save
the declaration".
</P>
<P>
Vedrine accused Netanyahu of adopting a "catastrophic policy"
toward the Palestinians and had driven the latter to the
"unprecedented level of exasperation and despair".
</P>
<P>
Peres said that he also discussed with Jospin his plan to
launch a joint economic aid program for Palestinian cities by
Israel and Europe.
</P>
<P>
The plan includes economic aid by eight Israeli cities and
eight European cities (four French and four German) to eight
Palestinian cities, he said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
