<HEADLINE> Svorada Wins Stage as Zulle Retains Jersey </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MADRID, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Jan Svorada gave the Czech
Republic their first stage win in the Tour of Spain while
defending champion Alex Zulle held onto the overall leader's
yellow jersey as the race reached Plasencia on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The 29-year-old Svorada, who won two stages of the Tour of
Catalonia and a stage in the Tour of Portugal earlier in the
summer, outsprinted the 1988 world champion Maurizio Fondriest of
Italy by about a length.
</P>
<P>
France's world cycling number one Laurent Jalabert in third
after a tough riding of 194.5 kilometers in the 11th stage.
</P>
<P>
The overall standings remained unchanged as Zulle, the reigning
world time-trial champion, leads compatriot Laurent Dufaux, who
was runner-up to Zulle last year in this race, by just over 30
seconds. Spaniard Fernando Escartin was in third over two minutes
behind.
</P>
<P>
The riders have a rest day on Wednesday before racing resumes
at Leon on Thursday. 
</P>
