<HEADLINE> Zimbabwe to Host Workshop on Exporting Fruits </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HARARE, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Zimbabwe Investment
Center (ZIC) is to host a workshop next week to explore
opportunities for partnership in the export of processed fruits
and vegetables from east and southern Africa with European
counterparts.
</P>
<P>
ZIC's Public Relations Manager Bekithemba Mhlanga today said
the workshop, to be held in conjunction with the Brussels-based
Center for the Development of Industry (CDI), will to be held in
Nyanga, northern Zimbabwe from September 22 to 25.
</P>
<P>
The workshop will be attended by delegates from Swaziland,
Tanzania, Kenya, Uganda, Mozambique, Germany, Italy, Spain,
Sweden, the Netherlands and Zimbabwe.
</P>
<P>
Mhlanga said, "During the workshop, delegates will discuss the
status of the European Union as a market for processed fruits and
vegetables quality control management and packaging technologies,
investment financing-sources and facilities available and export
credit and guarantee financing."
</P>
<P>
The workshop, he said, is expected to benefit producers and
processors in the industry to get a first hand account from the
importers on the latest trends and demands for processed fruits
by the EU market. 
</P>
