<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iranian President Voices Support to Lebanon </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Iranian President Mohammad
Khatami today voiced support to Lebanon and hoped that Lebanon
would become more stronger to stand against Israel.
</P>
<P>
In a meeting with visiting Lebanese Parliament Speaker Nabih
Berri, Khatami said that not only Lebanon's domestic unity is
needed but also Muslim and Arab world is required to stand by
Lebanon so as to achieve the goal.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian president noted that south Lebanon pays the
heaviest price for the Israeli aggressions and the people in
south Lebanon are resisting bravely.
</P>
<P>
He added that "the aggressive and expansionist nature of the
Zionist regime is the greatest danger to the region."
</P>
<P>
On the upcoming joint military exercise of the U.S., Turkey and
Israel and the Middle East and North Africa Economic Summit
scheduled to be held in Qatar in November with participation of
Israel, he said "such moves are aimed at sowing discord among the
Muslims."
</P>
<P>
The 54-year-old president warned "the enemies are trying to
sow discord among the Arab and Muslim states in a bid to
strengthen the position of Zionism."
</P>
<P>
He noted that the joint military exercise was not only an
insult to the regional nations but also a threat to the peace,
stability and the development of the region.
</P>
<P>
Khatami expressed his hope that the Qatari government would
cancel the scheduled summit in the interest of Qatar and the
entire region.
</P>
<P>
Nabih Berri arrived here Monday and held talks with Iranian
Foreign Minister Kamal Kharrazi and his Iranian counterpart Ali
Akbar Nateq-Nouri on bilateral ties, key regional issues and
developments in Lebanon Monday evening. 
</P>
</TEXT>
