<BODY>
<HEADLINE> 29 Children Killed in Egypt's Road Accident </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Twenty-nine children were
killed and 54 others injured a truck ran off a road and overturned
in north of Cairo today, the Middle East News Agency (MENA)
reported.
</P>
<P>
Police said the victims were travelling to work when their
truck rolled into a canal in the village of Maseer, near Kafr
el-Sheikh, 120 kilometers north of Cairo.
</P>
<P>
MENA said the driver, who was unharmed, lost control of the
truck after one of the tires busted.
</P>
<P>
Those children, between 14 and 17 in age, worked as spare hands
in the government-owned cotton fields in Kafr el-Sheikh. The
victims were rushed to a nearby hospital.
</P>
<P>
Child labor is common in this country with a population
of 60 million. According to International Monetary Fund (IMF)
statistics, 17 percent of its workforce are jobless. 
</P>
</TEXT>
