<HEADLINE> Portuguese-speaking Defense Experts Meet in </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Defense experts from the
Community of Portuguese-speaking Countries met here today to make
preparations for a ministerial meeting due to be held in Lisbon,
capital of Portugal in November.
</P>
<P>
Carlos Tembe, a spokesman for the meeting and an official from
the Defense Ministry of mozambique, said, "We hope this
meeting will contribute to exchanges and cooperation in the field
of military between member states of the Community of
Portuguese-speaking Countries."
</P>
<P>
There have been fewer military contacts between its members
since the community was set up in 1991, he said, adding that
Mozambique will benefit from bilateral or multi-lateral military
cooperation in the community.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, which will end on Wednesday, was attended by
defense experts from Mozambique, Brazil, Cape Verde, Angola,
Guinea Bissau, Portugal and Sao Tome &AMP; Principe.
</P>
<P>
The Mozambique Information Agency reported today that the
meeting of defense ministers of the community to be held in
Lisbon in November will discuss, among other topics, setting up a
peace-keeping force. 
