<HEADLINE> Eldoret Airport to Open for Flights Tomorrow </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NAIROBI, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Kenya's newly-built Eldoret
International Airport is scheduled to witness the landing of its
first passenger airline on September 17.
</P>
<P>
A program guide released by the African Airlines International
Company said that the weekly flights will connect Eldoret with
Sharja in Saudi Arabia and Karachi in Pakistan.
</P>
<P>
Another route will connect Eldoret with major cities in the
Great Lakes region, it said, adding that regular flights will be
on Mondays, Wednesdays, Fridays and Saturdays.
</P>
<P>
The construction of the airport which stands on a 975 acre
land started in January 1995 and the airport, 15 kilometers
southwest of Eldoret town in western Kenya, is designed with
facilities to handle any type of aircraft including the Boeing
747.
</P>
<P>
Last November Kenyan President Daniel arap Moi witnessed the
landing of the maiden flight to Eldoret International Airport,
the third international airport in the east African country.
</P>
<P>
Local leaders predicted that the airport will stimulate
tourism, horticultural farmings and other allied business in the
west parts of the country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
