<TEXT>
<P>
ADDIS ABABA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Organization of
African Unity (OAU) today donated 175,000 U.S.Dollars to three
African countries in support of their efforts to provide
assistance to refugees in their respective countries.
</P>
<P>
According to an OAU press release issued here, OAU Secretary
General Salim Ahmed Salim presented a cheque of 75,000
U.S.Dollars to Guinea which was hosting, under very difficult
circumstance, thousands of refugees from Liberia and Sierra
Leone.
</P>
<P>
The governments of Tanzania and Zambia also received 50,000
U.S. Dollars each at a ceremony here.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at the ceremony, the OAU Secretary General pointed
out that the donation is a symbolic gesture and a show of
solidarity and commitment of the OAU to encourage the countries
hosting refugees.
</P>
<P>
In response, the three ambassadors who received the cheques on
behalf of their respective governments expressed appreciation to
the OAU for its understanding of the deplorable situation faced
by the refugees in those countries, the OAU press release added.
