<HEADLINE> German Railroads Revenues Up 5.1 Percent in First Half </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, September 16 (Xinhua) -- German railroads revenues
increased by 5.1 percent to 4.7 billion marks (2.65 billion U.S.
dollars) in the first half of this year, the Wiesbaden-based
Federal Statistics Office reported today.
</P>
<P>
It said that during the period, the number of long-distance
rail travellers grew by 2.3 percent to 72 million, while that of
commuter rail passengers rose by 0.5 percent to 786 million.
</P>
<P>
The office attributed the improved revenues chiefly to the
ticket price increase. Prices was raised by 1.4 percent in western
Germany and by 4.8 percent in eastern Germany in February.
</P>
