<HEADLINE> Jordanian Crown Prince Visits Saudi Arabia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUWAIT CITY, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Jordanian Crown Prince
Hassan Ibn Talal arrived in the Red Sea port city of Jeddah today
on a two-day official visit to Saudi Arabia in a bid to improve
bilateral relations, Kuwait News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Hassan, who is accompanied by a high-ranking delegation
including Foreign Minister Fayez Tarawneh, paid the visit at the
invitation of Saudi Crown Prince and Deputy Prime Minister Prince
Abdullah Ibn Abdel-Aziz, the report said.
</P>
<P>
During his stay in Saudi Arabia, Hassan and his Saudi
counterpart Abdel-Aziz are expected to hold talks on further
improving relations between the two countries that became
estranged from each other following the Gulf war which was
triggered off by Iraqi invasion of Kuwait in 1990.
</P>
<P>
During the Gulf war, Saudi Arabia and other Arab countries
sided with Kuwait, while Jordan and Palestine supported Iraq.
</P>
<P>
Relations between the two countries made a breakthrough in
1996 when Jordanian King Hussein visited Saudi Arabia and met
King Fahd Ibn Abdul-Aziz. Hussein made his second visit to the
Gulf Kingdom last January.
</P>
<P>
Jordan has also inched to a restoration of relations with Kuwait
as the two countries have exchanged visits of officials over the
past two years and resumed direct air links last July.
</P>
<P>
Diplomatic sources were quoted as saying Hassan is likely to
hold talks with Fahd on the latest development in the Middle East
region.
</P>
<P>
Prince Hassan's visit to Saudi Arabia came two days after the
end of U.S. Secretary of State Madeleine Albright's visit to the
region, which took her to Israel, the Palestinian self-rule
areas, Syria, Egypt, Saudi Arabia, Jordan and Lebanon. 
</P>
</TEXT>
