<HEADLINE> Camerounian Governors Brace for Presidential </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YAOUNDE, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Tsoungui Gilber, Camerounian
Minister in charge of Territorial Administration today spoke
highly of his people's political maturity and profound attachment
to the ideals of peace, harmony and progress.
</P>
<P>
Gilber, who doubles as a vice premier, made the statement to
the country's ten provincial governors here today while opening
their first semester conference for the 1997/1998 fiscal year.
</P>
<P>
The current governor conference will be preoccupied by two
major topics, an evaluation on the organization of the
legislative elections and the preparation for the upcoming
presidential elections.
</P>
<P>
