encountered in organizing the May 17, 18 and August 3 legislative
elections. This is expected to pave way for organizational
strategies geared toward a hitch-free presidential election
billed for October.
</P>
<P>
Other issues to be discussed at the conference would be the
assessment of voters' registration.
</P>
<P>
The last conference of governors held in March this year had
focused on security matters. Although the circumstances under
which today's conference is convened may not be the same, public
security, peace and tranquility would still be the concern for
the governors.
</P>
<P>
The governors will also assess the implementation of the
decisions made at the 18th meeting held in March. 
