<HEADLINE> Police Station in Northern Ireland Damaged by Bomb </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A police station in Northern
Ireland was badly damaged by bomb today, the BBC television
reported.
</P>
<P>
The blast at Markethill, Co Armagh, came as police were
clearing the area.
</P>
<P>
There were no reports of injures, but several people were
treated for shock.
</P>
<P>
The bomb is believed to have been placed in a blue transit van
outside the station.
</P>
<P>
None has admitted the attack but it has disrupted multi-party
talks on the future of Northern Ireland.
</P>
<P>
The Ulster Unionists want Sinn Fein, the political arm of the
Irish Republican Army (IRA), to be thrown out of the multi-party
talks.
</P>
<P>
But the IRA has said it is not responsible for the bomb attack.
</P>
<P>
Northern Ireland security minister Adam Ingram said it was too
early to establish which group was responsible.
</P>
<P>
He said he wanted to fully establish the facts before making a
judgement. 
</P>
</TEXT>
