<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> US Industrial Production Rises Strongly in August </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The industrial production
in the U.S. increased by 0.7 percent in August, the U.S. Federal
Reserve (Fed) reported today.
</P>
<P>
The Fed said that the strong advance in production pushed the
operating rate at U.S. factories, mines and utilities to 83.9
percent of capacity, the highest since September 1995.
</P>
<P>
Manufacturing output increased by 1 percent in August after a
0.5 percent gain in July. The increase -- the most since April
1996 -- pushed the operating rate at U.S. factories to 83.1
percent, also the highest since September 1995.
</P>
<P>
The acceleration in U.S. industrial production between July and
August was concentrated in manufacturing, much of which was
related to the 10 percent jump in the assembly of autos and light
trucks, the report said.
</P>
<P>
Led by a 2.1 percent advance in the production of durable
goods, the overall output of consumer goods grew 0.6 percent in
the month. The production of nondurable goods increased by 0.3
percent.
</P>
<P>
But the operating rate at U.S. mines decreased by 1.0
percentage points in August to 92.2 percent, while the rate at
utilities was down by 1.1 percentage points to 87.4 point.
</P>
<P>
Some analysts said that it's time to get concerned when the
operating rate in the U.S. factories, mines and utilities is above
83 percent of capacity. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0074 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Canada's Defense Industry Employs 50,000: Study </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
OTTAWA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- A new study has found that
Canada's defense industry employs up to 50,000 people and
generated more than 5 billion Canadian dollars (3.6 billion US
dollars) in sales last year alone.
</P>
<P>
Quebec and Ontario, particularly the Ottawa area, accounted for
a substantial number of defense jobs, according to the study
released today.
</P>
<P>
The study, commissioned by the Canadian Defense Preparedness
Association (CDPA), indicated that the defense industry directly
employed 28,619 workers last year in 1,500 defense-related firms.
</P>
<P>
With economic spinoffs, about 50,000 jobs depend on the
industry across the country.
</P>
<P>
The CDPA, which represents Canadian companies in defense work,
commissioned the study because it is unhappy about the way the
sector is categorized in government data.
</P>
<P>
Ottawa needs more accurate information about the defense sector
because of impending policy decisions about restructuring Canada's
military, the CDPA said.
</P>
<P>
The CDPA clearly hopes to use the study to influence the
shaping of the country's defense industry policy. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
