<HEADLINE> Common People Praise Jiang's Report (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin's report to the
the 15th National Congress of the Communist Party of China, which
began on September 12, has been a daily topic of conversation
amongst common Chinese people who have benefited from the reform
and opening effort.
</P>
<P>
Most share the view that the report has instilled greater
confidence about the third generation leadership of the CPC with
Jiang Zemin at the core, who have pledged to uphold the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory and continue the reform and opening
drive initiated by Deng.
</P>
<P>
"Jiang told the congress that Chinese people have witnessed the
greatest ever improvements in their living standards over the past
five years," according to Qiang Ziqiang, an engineer from
Shanghai. "We feel it personally and foreigners visiting my family
are fully cognizant of the fact."
</P>
<P>
Qiang's residence is known as a so-called "open house" in
Shanghai, the largest metropolitan area in China. Qiang's family
has hosted over 20,000 foreign visitors who want to learn about
the daily life of an ordinary Chinese family since 1980s.
</P>
<P>
"Our country has adhered to a development goal and a constant
ideological direction," said Qiang, adding that people's lives
have been enriched, along with their access to knowledge and
entertainment.
</P>
<P>
Qiang spoke highly of Jiang's special note on economic
diversity based on the state economy.
</P>
<P>
Qiang's family, in fact, represents a "diverse economy". He and
his wife retired from state enterprises. Their eldest son works in
a Sino-foreign joint venture, while their second son, who
completed his studies abroad, has opened his own company, and
their daughter, the youngest of the three children, works for a
state firm.
</P>
<P>
"All Chinese, both young and old, regard the reform and opening
policy as good luck," said Qiang.
</P>
</TEXT>
