<HEADLINE> Common People Praise Jiang's Report (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Wu Yaoyao, an official in a community center in Shanghai's
Luwan District, told Xinhua that ordinary people are especially
excited at Jiang's report which touched on two crucial issues --
reemployment and fighting corruption.
</P>
<P>
Hao Peisheng, an employee of the Shanghai Southern Railway
Station, said: "Despite the fact that I did not have much
schooling, I pay great attention to state affairs. I fully support
Jiang's pledge to hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory."
</P>
<P>
Locals in Wenzhou, east China's Zhejiang Province which is
widely viewed as a pioneering reform city, have expressed profound
feelings about the ongoing Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
"Please convey my greetings to the Party Central Committee and
tell them we're grateful for the 15th Party Congress and to the
good policies of state." said Wu Xiaomei.
</P>
<P>
Wu started her business recycling plastic products. She
currently owns property valued at over 10 million yuan and last
year alone paid taxes of over 980,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
"Business people in Wenzhou have taken advantage of
opportunities since the country adopted the reform and opening
policies," said Wu, adding that she believes that the policy will
be further expanded after the Party Congress and the private
economy will enjoy further development.
</P>
<P>
The Handan Steel Complex, in north China's Hebei Province, a
reform model for state companies, has increased its capital assets
from less than 100 million yuan in the 1970s to well over nine
billion yuan.
</P>
