<HEADLINE> China to Organize First International Service Trade Group </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China announced today that
five Shanghai-based state-owned foreign trade companies will join
hands and organize the country's first international service
trade group.
</P>
<P>
Zhu Xiaoming, director of the Shanghai Foreign Economic
Relations and Trade Commission, who is here attending the ongoing
15th National Party Congress, said the new enterprise group will
be established later this month.
</P>
<P>
The five companies are the Shanghai Foreign Services Co. Ltd,
Shanghai Arts and Crafts Import and Export Corporation, Shanghai
Advertising Co. Ltd, Shanghai Foreign Economic Relations and Trade
Industrial Co. and Shanghai Foreign Economic and Trade and
Exhibition Co..
</P>
<P>
These five companies' sales volume in 1996 hit a total of 2.751
billion yuan with their total assets reaching 2.635 billion yuan,
495 million yuan of which were in net assets.
</P>
<P>
Though Shanghai is short of natural resources, it has lots of
talents and this is very good for developing service trades such
as finance, posts and telecommunications, transportation,
consultancy, tourism, and real estate, international service trade
in particular.
</P>
<P>
The establishment of the new enterprise group will facilitate
the city to participate in competition at the domestic and
international markets to promote the development of service
industry, he said.  
</P>
