<HEADLINE> Violent Crimes Increase in Pretoria, S. Africa </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JOHANNESBURG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Violent crimes have
been increasing in Pretoria, the administrative capital of South
Africa, local daily quoted police sources as reporting today.
</P>
<P>
Armed robberies and hijacking have shown a dramatic increase
of 76 percent and 47 percent respectively in the city in August,
comparing with the same period last year, Corrie Naude, the
Pretoria area police commander, said.
</P>
<P>
Pretoria had 174 car and truck hijackings from June to August
this year and 498 armed robberies during the same period, Naude
said, noting that it had caused major concern among the police
that violent crime from Johannesburg is spilling over Pretoria.
</P>
<P>
Johannesburg, about 50 km south of Pretoria, is one of the
major cities in South Africa where crimes and violent activities
have become rampant in recent years.  
</P>
