<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Mozambican President Urges to Raise Productivity </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Mozambican President Joaquim
Chissano has urged his countrymen to raise productivity in their
struggle against poverty and starvation.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a mass rally in Buzi county, Sofala province
Tuesday, Chissano urged Mozambicans to tap local conditions in
their production development, not waiting for external aid.
</P>
<P>
According to Noticias, a newspaper published in Maputo today,
the president said that people in the country could only expect
to improve their life quality when they have turned out products.
</P>
<P>
Grain production and clothing were noted by Chinssano as the
first two to be developed in the country.
</P>
<P>
Sofala is one of the key economic provinces in the country.
The province managed a one percent growth in the first half of
the year over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
This is Chissano's first visit to the province this year.
</P>
</TEXT>
