<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Disabled Reaches One Million in Mozambique </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MAPUTO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of disabled people
reached one million in Mozambique among its total 18 million
population, the Mozambican News Agency reported today.
</P>
<P>
Farida Gulamo, Secretary-General of the Association of the
Disabled in Mozambique (ADEMO) was quoted as saying Tuesday that
the number is still growing in the country which had been plagued
by abject poverty and the aftermath of prolonged civil war in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Speaking at a national function on disabled, Gulamo said that
most of the disabled in the country are among the poorest,
especially women and children, they could not enjoy equal rights
in education, employment and law.
</P>
<P>
Gulamo said, the 1989-established ADEMO has worked for
training, donation, distributing food to the disabled and
maintaining their rights. 
</P>
</TEXT>
