<HEADLINE> Beijing Youth Eager to Join Communist Party (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Liu Yang entered prestigious
Beijing University and one of the first major decision he made was
to apply for membership of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
Liu responded to a question in the application by saying that
"The Communist Party of China is a great political party, and only
the Party can lead the Chinese people to prosperity."
</P>
<P>
Liu said the 15th CPC National Congress which is meeting from
Sept. 12-18 "has established the precept of raising high the great
banner of Deng Xiaoping's Theory and propelling the cause of
building socialism with Chinese characteristics into the 21st
century."
</P>
<P>
"This represents the aspirations of the entire nation, and
further increases my confidence in the Party," said Liu.
</P>
<P>
Liu is only one of a growing contingent of young people in the
Chinese capital who are actively applying for membership in the
CPC, with over 20,000 young people joining the Party every year.
</P>
<P>
In Beijing University alone, some 2,000 students have applied
for Party membership each and every year since the beginning of
1990s, according to Hou Xuezhong, the official in charge of
Beijing University's CPC committee.
</P>
<P>
Hou noted that the number of applicants continues to grow, with
some 3,628 students submitting applications in 1996. The figure
accounted for a quarter of the university's then total enrollment.
</P>
<P>
The university's Party organization has admitted 3,116 new
members since 1991, including 2,849 students, said Hou.
</P>
<P>
Party members accounted for 9.33 percent of the school's
undergraduate population in the first six months of this year, up
from 5.3 percent in 1991. The figure for Graduate students
accounted for 22.6 of the total.
</P>
<P>
The number of students applying for Party membership at other
Beijing universities has also grown in recent years, with Party
members accounting for around ten percent of the total number of
students in schools like Qinghua University and the Chinese
People's University.
</P>
</TEXT>
