<HEADLINE> Malaysia Sets Up Funds to Upgrade Technology </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KUALA LUMPUR, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Malaysia today launched
two funds to further accelerate and upgrade the development of
indigenous technological capabilities.
</P>
<P>
The funds -- the Commercialization of R&AMP;D (research and
development) Fund and the Technology Acquisition Fund -- will be
managed by Malaysian Technology Development Corporation (MTDC) and
are open to all Malaysian companies, including small and
medium-sized industries (SMIs), International Trade and Industry
Minister Rafidah Aziz said.
</P>
<P>
A sum of 100 million ringgit (about 33.3 million U.S. dollars)
has been allocated for the Commercialization of R&AMP;D Fund and 61
million ringgit (about 20.3 million dollars) for the Technology
Acquisition Fund, she said when launching the funds, according to
the Malaysian national news agency Bernama.
</P>
<P>
The funds will provide partial grants ranging from 50 percent
to 70 percent, she said.
</P>
<P>
For the Commercialization of R&AMP;D Fund, joint ventures between
local firms and universities/public research institutions, both
local and foreign, are also eligible to apply.
</P>
<P>
She urged all Malaysian companies to fully tap the fund and
step up R&AMP;D efforts in order to enhance their competitiveness and
capabilities against more technologically-advanced entities.
</P>
</TEXT>
