<HEADLINE> Iran Conducts Aerial Maneuver </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Iranian Air Force is carrying
out a three-day aerial maneuver code-named Thunder-9 involving
150 fighters, Air Force Commander Brigadier General Habib Baqaie
said here today.
</P>
<P>
The commander assessed the aerial maneuver, which started from
Tuesday, as "positive" and "displaying the force's highest level
of combat readiness in defending the country."
</P>
<P>
"The maneuver aims to strengthen the combat readiness of the
Air Force personnel," he was quoted by the official news agency
IRNA as saying.
</P>
<P>
However, the commander did not mention where the maneuver is
being carried out or what kinds of jet fighters were used in the
operations.
</P>
<P>
Electronics warfare and radar detections are focus of the
maneuver's programs, aiming to boost the force's readiness for
defending vital economic resources of the country, according to
the IRNA.
</P>
<P>
The commander said the maneuver is "unprecedented" in terms of
the extent of operations, the massive forces involved and the
high-technology equipment deployed.
</P>
<P>
He added that despite its extensive scale, the maneuver has
not resulted in any casualties. 
</P>
