<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Iran Bolsters up Lebanon against Israel </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TEHRAN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Iran's Supreme Leader Ali
Khamenei today bolstered up Lebanon in its fight against Israeli
aggression while promising continuous support.
</P>
<P>
While meeting with visiting Lebanese Parliament Speaker
Nabih Berri, Khamenei described the anti-Israeli resistance in
Southern Lebanon as a source of honor and prestige for the Arab
and Islamic world.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian leader also stressed unity and solidarity against
the "Zionist enemy."
</P>
<P>
Turning to efforts made by Israel and other enemies of Islam
to sow discord among Muslims, Khamenei said that Shiite and
Sunni Muslims were enjoying a harmonious coexistence in Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
He told his Lebanese guest that any action which may help the
enemy to sow discord among Muslims must be refrained from.
</P>
<P>
Khamenei also referred to the smear campaign waged by Israel
to accuse Lebanese Muslim youths of terrorist acts, saying all
freedom-loving people of the world know well that these faithful
youths are defending their dignity, independence and homeland.
</P>
<P>
According to a report carried by the official news agency
IRNA, Khamenei also touched on the close ties between Iran and
Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Berri who arrived here Monday said that the anti-Zionist
resistance has created unity and solidarity among all Lebanese
groups and the government and shattered the ranks of Zionist
enemy.
</P>
<P>
He also praised the supports offered by Iran to Lebanon.
</P>
<P>
Before his departure at the airport today, Berri said, "Iran
is a powerful country in the region, which can play a
fundamental role in solving the problems of the region."
</P>
</TEXT>
