<HEADLINE> More People Visit Deng's Former Home </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- An increasing number of
people have visited the former residence of Deng Xiaoping in
Guang'an County, Sichuan Province, since the 15th Congress of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) was convened on September 12.
</P>
<P>
A member of the local administrative staff reports that the
daily number of visitors has increased three-fold.
</P>
<P>
He said that many of the visitors have journeyed from other
parts of the country specially for the occasion. On a visitor's
book, a visitor wrote: "It is especially memorable to visit Deng's
former home and review his great life and achievements during the
ongoing 15th Party Congress."
</P>
<P>
The administrative staff made special arrangements for the
occasion by preparing a brief introduction to Deng's life, and a
photo exhibit of the third generation of CPC leadership.
</P>
<P>
A wide-screen color television in the courtyard allows both
staff workers and visitors to monitor the progress of the Party
Congress.
</P>
<P>
"Jiang Zemin's work report at the congress fully confirms the
authoritative status of Deng Xiaoping's Theory and has greatly
inspired people to visit Deng's former home," according to Xu
Xiuwen, an agronomist from Beijing.
</P>
<P>
Newlyweds Jiang Qijian and Huang Xiuli journeyed from Shenzhen,
the country's first special economic zone set up in the early 80s
under Deng's proposal. "Shenzhen has been evolved from a former
wasteland into a modern metropolis under the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory," said Jiang.
</P>
<P>
"We are fully confident and determined that the third
generation of the CPC leadership with Jiang Zemin at the core is
capable of leading the people to build the motherland well and
unite the people of different nationalities," said Losang, a young
man from the Tibet Autonomous Region. 
</P>
