<HEADLINE> Intl. Auto Exhibition Opens in Northeast China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGCHUN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- An international exhibition
of automobiles, auto parts and maintenance equipment opened today
in Changchun, capital of northeast China's Jilin Province,
</P>
<P>
The five-day showcase event, which has attracted more than 170
manufacturers from more than 10 countries and regions, is expected
to help expand Sino-foreign technological cooperation in the
automobile sector.
</P>
