<HEADLINE> Pakistani Leaders Condemn Killing of Iranian Trainees </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Both Pakistani Prime
Minister Nawaz Sharif and President Farooq Leghari today condemned
the killing of five Iranian Air Force trainees by unidentified
gunmen in Pakistan and expressed profound grief over the incident.
</P>
<P>
"On behalf of the government and people of Pakistan, I should
like to express sentiments of profound shock, grief and
indignation over the senseless attack," Sharif said in a
condolence message to Iranian President Syed Muhammad Khatami.
</P>
<P>
The Iranian trainees, who came here in August for a two-month
training course, were shot dead this morning by unidentified
gunmen in Rawalpindi. The Iranians' Pakistani driver was also
killed.
</P>
<P>
"While strongly condemning this brutal act, I should like to
assure Your Excellency that we shall endeavor our utmost to arrest
those responsible and award them exemplary punishment," Sharif
said.
</P>
<P>
"Relations between Pakistan and Iran rest on the solid
foundations of our Islamic faith, a shared cultural heritage and
coincidence of interests on the major issues of our time," he
added.
</P>
<P>
"We are confident that no dastardly act of terrorism can affect
our time-tested friendship which serves the larger interests of
the two brotherly peoples."
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, President Leghari also sent a message to the Iranian
president to express deep shock and outrage over the tragic
killing.
</P>
<P>
Leghari said in his message, "We shall not spare any effort to
apprehend those guilty of this crime and to mete out exemplary
punishment to them."
</P>
<P>
The perpetrators of this sickly act, he said, can never succeed
in subverting the abiding and time-tested relationship between
Pakistan and Iran.
</P>
<P>
The Pakistani president said his country remains committed to a
close cooperative relationship with Iran and shall work closely
with the Iranian government in defeating the nefarious objectives
of what he called the criminal terrorists.  
</P>
</TEXT>
