<HEADLINE> Xi'an Investment and Trade Fair Concludes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XI'AN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A total of 112 contracts for
foreign-funded projects were signed during the six-day investment
and trade fair which ended today in Xi'an, capital of northwest
China's Shaanxi Province.
</P>
<P>
The projects will involve total investments of 642 million US
dollars, including 381 million US dollars in overseas investment.
</P>
<P>
In addition, domestic investors will provide nearly 3.7 billion
yuan in funding for the construction of 200 local projects.
</P>
<P>
The city will cooperate with investors from Hong Kong and
Germany to construct a 30-million US dollar waterworks, the city's
first infrastructure construction project involving foreign
investment.
</P>
<P>
19 foreign-funded projects involve contracted investments of
over 10 million US dollars each, with an additional 11 projects
involving five million US dollars each.
</P>
<P>
Contracts for six agricultural projects will involve a total of
some 26 million US dollars.
</P>
<P>
The annual investment and trade fair attracted over 1,000
participants from more than 30 countries and regions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
