by good United States economic data and a rise on Wall Street.
</P>
<P>
"The positive economic data, which enforced low inflation and
reduced the likelihood of an interest rate rise in the US, was a
major influence in the local market," said dealer Scott Emms from
Henderson Jones.
</P>
<P>
The all ordinaries index closed 27.5 points higher at 2,679.3.
</P>
<P>
The all resources index finished 3.5 points higher at 1,330.3,
while the all industrials index was 56.3 points higher at 4,395.4.
</P>
<P>
Resource giant BHP was up nine cents at 16.19 Australian
dollars, fellow resources major WMC closed steady at 6.35
Australian dollars.
</P>
<P>
Banking and insurance stocks finished strongly as investors
sought shares that offered high yield and security.
</P>
<P>
National Australia Bank closed 33 cents up, ANZ Bank was up 24
cents, Westpac Bank gained two cents and Commonwealth Bank rose 19
cents.
</P>
<P>
The gold index was down 0.4 points at 1,252.4 with Normandy
down one cent and Plutonic Resources up one cent.
</P>
<P>
National turnover was 405.20 million shares valued at 1.127
million Australian dollars (811.44 million US dollars) with rises
of 664 outnumbering falls of 524.  
