<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Police Discover Tamil Arms Cache </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A large cache of weapons for
use by Tamil suicide bombers were discovered on Tuesday night
outside the capital city of Colombo, the local press reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The discovery was made after two leaders of the Liberation
Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) were taken into custody by the police
of Mount Lavinia at the suburb of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
Around a dozen suicide LTTE cadres had got away before police
arrived, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The weapons, including explosives, hand grenades and some
jackets which suicide bombers may wear in action, were found in a
house at Raja Mawatha, Ratmalana, a small town 20 kilometers south
of Colombo.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels paid a rent of 9,000 rupees (153 U.S. dollars)
per month for the house, which was quite expensive by local
standards, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
Initial investigation indicated that the rebels were targeting
the Ratmalana Airport, the Colombo Harbor, the Air Force
detachment and the Army headquarters in Colombo.  
</P>
</TEXT>
