<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0157 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang's Report Guides Reunification: Scholars </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
FUZHOU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Experts and scholars on Taiwan
Question in east China's Fujian Province have expressed their full
support for the ideas and principles concerning the country's
reunification set forth in Comrade Jiang Zemin's report at the
ongoing National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
At a forum held here Tuesday afternoon by the Provincial Taiwan
Affair Office, the scholars noted that it is of great importance
that Jiang highlighted the peaceful reunification issue in his
opening report.
</P>
<P>
Deputy Director of Fujian Taiwan Affairs Office Liang Maogan
said Jiang's report has enriched and expanded the "one country,
two systems" concept set forth by Deng Xiaoping. It will guide
us to hold high the great banner of Deng's theory and advance the
process of the motherland's peaceful reunification, he said.
</P>
<P>
Being in close geographic proximity, Fujian province and
Taiwan share the same culture including customs and dialect, which
has accounted for the long-standing good relations between people
across the Taiwan Strait, he noted.
</P>
<P>
Liang reviewed the work Fujian has done in recent years to
promote the reunification cause. He said Hong Kong's smooth return
to the motherland and the continued stability and prosperity were
examples for the settlement of the Taiwan issue based on the
principle of "one country, two systems."
</P>
<P>
However, the development of Taiwan's separatist tendency and
the interference of foreign hostile forces have gravely threatened
the peaceful reunification process.
</P>
<P>
Pan Shuming, director of the Provincial Academy of Social
Sciences, said Jiang made clear in his report the Chinese
mainland's position, confidence, sincerity and determination with
regard to promoting the reunification cause.
</P>
<P>
He said that Taiwan authorities should respond with sincerity.
</P>
<P>
Wu Nengyuan, director of the province's Taiwan Research
Institute, said that the convention of the Party's 15th National
Congress and Jiang Zemin's report will help increase the Taiwan
people's confidence in the motherland's reunification.
</P>
<P>
As Comrade Jiang Zemin said in his report, Liang noted,
Taiwan's future lies in the reunification, and any attempt to
split the motherland will reach a dead end.
</P>
<P>
Liang said he was confident that no matter how many obstacles
there might be on the road to reunification, the people on both
sides of the Straits as well as the whole Chinese nation will
surely achieve their goal.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
