<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0169 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Presidium of Party Congress Holds Third Meeting </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The presidium of the 15th
National Congress of the Communist Party of China (CPC) held its
third meeting here today.
</P>
<P>
The meeting, presided over by Jiang Zemin, approved by a show
of hands lists of candidates for members and alternate members, of
a new CPC Central Committee, and candidates for members of a new
Central Commission for Discipline Inspection (CCDI) following a
marginal preliminary election, and they will be submitted to all
delegations for deliberations.
</P>
<P>
Starting from September 15, all delegations held full
deliberations about the lists of candidates for members and
alternate members, of a new CPC Central Committee, and candidate
for members of a new CCDI.
</P>
<P>
A marginal preliminary election of the members and alternate
members of a new CPC Central Committee and of members of the CCDI
was held yesterday afternoon and this morning.
</P>
<P>
The preliminary election was conducted under the supervision of
scrutineers in accordance with the election method of the
congress.
</P>
<P>
The 15th National Party Congress will hold its formal election
tomorrow morning.  
</P>
