<HEADLINE> Noted Party Scholar on China's Historic Opportunities (1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A noted scholar of the
Communist Party of China (CPC) expressed his belief that China
will achieve smooth development in the next century by promoting
reform and opening up and the modernization drive under the
leadership of CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
Gong Yuzhi, deputy director of the Party History Research
Office of the CPC Central Committee and vice-president of the
Party School of the Committee, made the the remarks by
comparing historic opportunities and challenges of the Party in
the last 60 years.
</P>
<P>
In the 1930s when Japanese imperialists invaded China, putting
the Chinese nation to the brink of subjugation, he said, the CPC
called on the entire country to wage a war of resistance against
Japanese aggression instead of fighting the civil war. The appeal
by the CPC resulted in a cooperation between the Communist Party
and the Kuomingtang.
</P>
<P>
As an important force to fight back the facists, the CPC has
safeguarded the national dignity of China and developed the
Party's strength in such a war.
</P>
<P>
In the historic test after the War of Resistance against Japan,
he said, the Communist Party of China won the heart of the Chinese
people by conforming to the aspiration of the nation. The move
ended the rule by Chiang Kai-shek and resulted in the
establishment of the new China.
</P>
</TEXT>
