<HEADLINE> Noted Party Scholar on China's Historic Opportunities (2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
However, Gong admitted the Party has also lost some historic
opportunities because of the "Great Leap Forward" and the ten
years of turmoil, or the "Cultural Revolution," widening the
development gap between China and the developed countries.
</P>
<P>
Over the recent 20 years, he said, China has grasped and made
good use of two historic opportunities, which resulted in the
economic booms today.
</P>
<P>
It was Deng Xiaoping who played a leading role in the last two
historic periods, one in the late 1970s after the downfall of the
Gang of Four, another in the late 1980s and the early 1990s.
</P>
<P>
The current world situation has been developing rapidly, Gong
said, adding although peace and development will be theme of the
times, the reorganization of different interest blocs and
integration of global economy will be accelerated. "We will feel
great pressure to bear upon if our development speed lags behind
other countries," he said.
</P>
<P>
Gong noted, "This is the historic background of the current
Party congress as well as the challenge facing the new generation
of collective leadership of China."
</P>
<P>
Some people are wondering after Deng Xiaoping's death whether
China can remain stable and whether the country can press on
with the reform and opening-up. Some others wish to see a chaotic
China. In this sense, the convocation of the 15th Party congress
is a historic conference in the historic period, he said.
</P>
<P>
The report Jiang Zemin delivered at the Party congress has
demonstrated the daring and resolution of the collective
leadership of the CPC Central Committee. The report, which has
observed and explained the current situation in a sober-minded
way, charted the right track with some breakthroughs.
</P>
<P>
"China will witness a smooth development in the next century if
we can seize the excellent opportunities," said Gong. 
</P>
