<HEADLINE> 3 Iranian Air Force Trainees Killed in Pakistan </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ISLAMABAD, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Five persons, including
three Iranian air force trainees, were shot dead and two others
seriously injured today by unidentified gunmen in the Pakistani
city of Rawalpindi, police said.
</P>
<P>
Three gunmen riding motorcycles opened fire with Kalashinkov
rifles this morning on a Toyota van, which was carrying five
Iranian air force trainees, at busy Chour Chowk in Rawalpindi, the
sister city of Islamabad.
</P>
<P>
The Iranians were on their way from the Kamra aeronautical
complex, some 70 kilometers west of Rawalpindi, to the Civil
Aviation Dhamial Camp in the city, the police said.
</P>
<P>
The driver of the van, Asif, and two Iranian trainees died on
the spot, the police said. Three other trainees and a passer-by
were injured.
</P>
<P>
One Iranian trainee and the passer-by succumbed to their
injuries on their way to hospital and the other two injured were
admitted in a local Hospital and their conditions are stated to be
critical, police added.
</P>
<P>
Officials of the district administration and police reached the
spot as soon as they heard about the incident. The police have
sealed off all the main points of the city to trace the unknown
culprits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
