<HEADLINE> Tung Chee Hwa on Future Role of Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Asia's economic and
political impact on the world in the decades to come cannot be
overlooked and Hong Kong remains a leading financial and service
center in the region, Chief Executive of the Hong Kong Special
Administrative Region (HKSAR) Tung Chee Hwa told an international
business community here today.
</P>
<P>
In his keynote address on the Sixth Annual World Economic
Development Congress, Tung Chee Hwa said that the East Asia Region
could have an economy larger than that of the North American Free
Trade Agreement (NAFTA) members or the European Union soon in the
21st century,
</P>
<P>
This region could produce 1,200 to 1,300 billion U.S. dollars
in additional annual savings than it does today, thereby becoming
one of the largest capital markets in the world, he said. He also
quoted a report by the Asian Development Bank (ADB) that estimates
the region will have spent almost 1,000 billion U.S. dollars in
investments in infrastructure projects alone by the year 2000,
</P>
<P>
That means "Asia may well emerge as the world's largest
producer, capital lender, and capital borrower, as well as the
world's largest consumer market," Tung said.
</P>
<P>
"Imagine the unlimited economic opportunities which will
present themselves in the coming decades as this region's economy
continues to grow and as China becomes one of the largest
economies in the world," the right place the international
business community should be located to take advantage of these
opportunities is here in Hong Kong, Tung asserted.
</P>
<P>
He pledged that Hong Kong will continue to provide a friendly
business environment and a world-class service to backup
international corporations doing businesses in Hong Kong, in China
and throughout Asia.
</P>
<P>
"Our Chinese heritage, Western management style, and ability to
speak English and Chinese have placed Hong Kong in the best
position to provide the international business community with the
people, the knowledge and the skills necessary to run successful
business in China and the rest of Asia," Tung explained to the
audience.
</P>
<P>
The Special Administrative Regional Government will work hard
to ensure that Hong Kong maintains its position as a leading
financial and service center and remains at the forefront of the
new age with cutting-edge new technology and new industries, the
chief executive promised, inviting the international business
community to play an active role in Hong Kong's continuing
prosperity and development.
</P>
<P>
The World Economic Development Congress was established in 1992
as a forum for the public and private sectors to interact and
discuss economic issues facing the world.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
