<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Theory of Primary Stage of Socialism Vital to China's Success (1) (By Zhao Hong) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- When peasants in Fengyang,
east China's Anhui Province, spearheaded the move in 1978 in China
to introduce the contract responsibility system in which
individual farming households has the final say in what to grow
and how to operate, the majority of Chinese were discussing
whether the practice is capitalist or socialist.
</P>
<P>
Although the success story of Fengyang convinced the Chinese
people, they din not get a systematic and theoretical answer until
1987 when the 13th Party Congress made an exposition of the theory
that China is in the primary stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
As an important cornerstone of Deng Xiaoping Theory, the
exposition of the primary stage of socialism has affirmed
socialist nature of Fengyang's experiment and other reform
initiatives elsewhere, making it clear that the relations of
production must be in agreement with the reality of China's low
productive forces.
</P>
<P>
The shareholding system and joint stock partnership which have
been introduced in China over the past few years have also raised
doubts among some people. They can get an answer from Jiang
Zemin's report to the on-going 15th National Congress of the
Communist Party of China -- it is because China is in the primary
stage of socialism.
</P>
<P>
It is ten years since the theory was put forward. Why has
China still been in the primary stage? Hasn't China moved
forward?
</P>
<P>
"China does have scored great achievements in economic
construction over the recent few years, which can be described as
China's great progress forward," said Xing Bensi, vice-president
of the Party School of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
However, Xing said China has been in a stage of
underdevelopment, or primary stage as the country has low
production level and poor foundation. "This stage will continue
for about 100 years," he said.
</P>
<P>
The 15th Party Congress has affirmed, in an all-round way, the
primary stage of socialism, he said, adding that China should use
all forms of ownership to serve socialism as long as they can help
expand the socialist economy. Shareholding system can be applied
in capitalism and so can be in socialism.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0197 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> News Analysis: Theory of Primary Stage of Socialism Vital to China's Success (2) (By Zhao Hong) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
As China's reform has entered a critical period in solving
deep-rooted contradictions, the report has, for the first time,
put forward the major tasks in economic restructuring to continue
readjustment and improving the ownership pattern.
</P>
<P>
The current congress has, for the first time, pointed out
that China should see the full meaning of the public sector,
experimenting with diversified forms of public ownership while
upholding the dominant position and competitive edge of the state
sector.
</P>
<P>
The congress has affirmed various cooperation forms in terms of
labor, capital and stock. It has also affirmed the coexistence of
different modes of distribution, which combines remuneration
according to work and remuneration according to factors of
production put in, keeping the former in a dominant position. "It
is realistic and to the point," said a congress delegate.
</P>
<P>
The affirmation of the primary stage of socialism in the
current conference is to convince the decision-makers at various
levels to gain a clear understanding of the reality and work out
goals and measures in accordance with the criteria of "three
favorables" -- favorable to promoting the growth of the productive
forces in a socialist society, increasing the overall strength
of the socialist country and raising people's living standards.
</P>
<P>
Efforts should be made to materialize public ownership that can
greatly promote the growth of the productive forces. All
management methods and organizational forms that accord with the
laws governing socialized production may be utilized boldly, the
report says.
</P>
<P>
"To hold high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping Theory in the
report by Comrade Jiang Zemin has reassured us that we are right
to adhere to the criteria in developing the productive forces,"
said Wang Yinping, a congress delegate from Fengyang, a village in
Anhui. 
</P>
</TEXT>
