<HEADLINE> Shenzhen Still Focus of Attention </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Li Youwei, Secretary of the
Shenzhen City Party Committee, has always been followed by Chinese
and overseas reporters whenever and wherever he appears during the
ongoing five-yearly 15th National Party Congress.
</P>
<P>
This shows that Shenzhen, China's first special economic zone
(SEZ), is still the focus of attention today when China
continues its reforms and opening-up.
</P>
<P>
Minutes prior to the opening session of the current congress,
reporters asked him what amazing measures Shenzhen is going to
take in the near future.
</P>
<P>
Li said people in Shenzhen are elated at Jiang Zemin's report
which called for holding high the great banner of Deng Xiaoping
Theory after they heard the live televised report by CCTV. "It is
of historical significance," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Shenzhen SEZ has developed under the guidance of Deng
Xiaoping Theory, he said, adding that people in Shenzhen have
built an internationally famous city on a vast uncultivated land
in 17 years.
</P>
<P>
"Therefore," he said, "we'll continue to hold high firmly Deng
Xiaoping Theory in years to future."
</P>
<P>
Every step and every measure Shenzhen takes in the course of
reforms would cause people's attention and provoke various outside
comments, he said.
</P>
<P>
The mixed ownership is Shenzhen's principal form of ownership,
which has enhanced the state-owned sector and increased its state
assets, he said.
</P>
<P>
Referring to the status of Shenzhen after Hong Kong's return to
the motherland, Li said: "Hong Kong's return has brought new
opportunities to Shenzhen." "With an improved infrastructure built
over the past decade and more, Shenzhen, encouraged by the
guidelines of the current Party congress, will continue to
emancipate the mind and make bold experiments," he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
