<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Indian Tread Rubber Firm Invests in Tanzania </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
DAR ES SALAAM, September 17 (Xinhua) -- An Indian firm, Elgi
Twiga, has invested 300,000 US dollars in a pre-cured tread
rubber manufacturing plant in Arusha, northern Tanzania,
according to a news dispatch reaching here today.
</P>
<P>
The project, which started trial production Monday, is capable
of serving all major retreaders who are currently importing the
tread rubber, the Company's Group Managing Director Sudarsan
Varadaraj was quoted as saying.
</P>
<P>
The company has three massive manufacturing facilities in
India with a total production capacity of 1,500 tons of tread
rubber per month. It has also small manufacturing facilities in
Kenya, Mauritius and Sri Lanka.
</P>
<P>
The project in Arusha, which will make use of local raw
materials such as natural rubber and packing materials, intends
later to start pre-cured tyre retreading plants throughout
Tanzania in order to popularize the technology.
</P>
<P>
The plant's production manager M. Venkatesan said the project
is a new venture with the primary objective of popularizing
pre-cured tyre retreading in Tanzania. When in full production,
the company intends to export its products to Rwanda, Burundi,
Zambia and Malawi.
</P>
<P>
Elgi Twiga is part of the group of companies of the giant
Indian manufacturers, Elgi Tyre and Tread Limited. 
</P>
</TEXT>
