<HEADLINE> World-Famous Hairstylist Looking at Chinese Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Shanghai, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Vidal Sassoon, one of the
big names in hair-care products, held a hairstyle show here
recently, and the city folks of Shanghai, Beijing, Guangzhou,
Nanjing, and Hanghou found themselves in an entirely new world.
</P>
<P>
Vidal Sassoon, who is now in his late 60s, has enjoyed
considerable prominence in international hairstyling and has
stayed out on fashions leading edge by improving cutting,
coloring, and perming.
</P>
<P>
There are 26 Sassoon beauty salons and a dozen Sassoon
institutes in the United States, Canada, Britain, and Germany, and
Sassoon is now planning on marketing his shampoo and other
products in China.
</P>
<P>
He said he has begun to be familiar with Chinese and Asian
facial features, and has designed a classic Sassoon hairstyle that
he calls the "Sassoon Bob" for Chinese women.
</P>
<P>
"I feel confident about China's economic development and the
improvment of living standards in China," he said.
</P>
<P>
The Sassoon Bob is supposed to help women get rid of the
over-elaborate hairstyle and is elabrate, simple and easy to do.
</P>
<P>
And the three-day beauty show was held in Shanghai and provided
training for 300 professional hair designers. 
</P>
