</P>
<P>
New Nigerian
</P>
<P>
-- Nigeria's defense headquarters said on Tuesday that 11
ECOMOG soldiers, mainly Nigerians, had been killed by land mines
planted by the Sierra Leonean military junta.
</P>
<P>
-- Overcrowding of Nigerian prisons has turned them into
"incubators of hardened criminals" rather than rehabilitation
places they are meant, according the chief of general staff
Lt.-Gen. Oladipo Diya.
</P>
<P>
Daily Times
</P>
<P>
-- Nigeria's head of state general Sani Abacha reassured on
Tuesday that his administration will quit office on October 1,
1998, in line with the transition to civil rule program.
</P>
<P>
This Day
</P>
<P>
-- Nigerian national drug law enforcement agency said on
Tuesday it arrested 3,754 drug suspects and seized 63,513.09 kg
of various narcotic drugs and psychotropic substnaces since 1994.
