<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Island to Hold Piano Festival </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
XIAMEN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- China's small "Island of
Pianos," Gulang Island in Xiamen, Fujian Province, will host a
piano music festival during September 27-29 to show its crazy
about the Western musical instrument.
</P>
<P>
The piano was first shipped to Gulang Island some 100 years
ago. Pianos now have become the most popular musical instrument on
the 1.8 square-kilometer island.
</P>
<P>
There are more than 400 pianos on the island, averaging one for
every ten families, ranking Gulang first in the country in terms
of piano density.
</P>
<P>
Many of China's noted pianists are natives of Gulang, which
possibly has contributed to the islanders' love of the instrument.
</P>
<P>
The festival will feature a series of concerts, performed by
both professional and amateur musicians.
</P>
<P>
A musical troupe from Russia will also take part in the event,
according to the local government. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
