<HEADLINE> Brazilian Crown at Beach Volleyball World Championsh </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Brazil took both the men's
and women's beach volleyball titles at the 1997 FIVB World
Championship in Los Angeles, the sport's governing body said on
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Para and Guiherme beat Whitmarsh and Ceman of the United States
5-12, 12-8, 12-10 to take the men's top honour, while compatriots
Olympic winners Jackie Silva and Sandra Pires won a one hour 29
minutes match against American champions Arce and Mcpeak 12-11,
1-12, 12-10.
</P>
<P>
Fifty-six men's teams from 21 countries and 46 women's teams
from 20 countries participated in the 600,000 US dollars World
Championships.
</P>
<P>
All matches were played at UCLA Bruins Tennis Center with sands
paved on the ground.
</P>
<P>
The beach volleyball has been included in the 2000 Sydney
Olympics. 
</P>
