<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Foreign Banks Gain Bigger Share of Credit Market in Vietnam </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign banks have been getting
record share in Vietnam's loan market, "Vietnam News" reported
today.
</P>
<P>
The loan market share for foreign banks in capital city of
Hanoi was nearly 50 percent in June, an increase of 70 percent
over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the loan market share for Vietnam's commercial banks
fell from 65 percent to 54.5 percent during the same period.
</P>
<P>
Banking experts said that foreign banks have been able to
expand their activities because they are allowed to do business in
Vietnamese currency.
</P>
<P>
They are ready to finance local enterprises with proven
credibility and business acumen, while the local banks are bound
by a series of rules and regulations, they added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
