<HEADLINE> Vietnam Gears Up For Copyright Agreement Implementation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HANOI, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Vietnam and the United States
are speeding up preparations for the implementation of an
agreement on copyright due to come into effect next January, the
newspaper "Vietnam News" reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The agreement, which was signed by U.S. State Secretary
Madeleine Albright and Vietnamese Foreign Minister Nguyen Manh Cam
last June, was established to protect copyright for motion
pictures, videos, musical performances and software.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam's Department of Copyright is preparing documents and
training sessions for various agencies and organizations,
especially in the motion picture and musical performance
industries.
</P>
<P>
Vietnam will strive to fulfill the requirements of the
agreement, first by preventing piracy of copyright and authorship,
said the report.
</P>
<P>
However, the English-language daily said, since the country's
legal system is underdeveloped, the enforcement of the new
agreement is expected to be difficult. 
</P>
</TEXT>
