<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0237 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Number of HK Drug Abusers Drops </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The number of drug abusers
in Hong Kong dropped by 13 percent in the first half of this year
to 11,060 compared with 12,719 reported in the same period last
year, a local newspaper said today.
</P>
<P>
The number of drug abusers under the age of 21 dropped 17.2
percent to 1,964 from 2,371, while that of female drug abusers
fell 12.6 percent to 1,305 from 1,493, the South China Morning
Post reported, quoting Clarie Lo Ku Ka-lee, the Commissioner for
Narcotics.
</P>
<P>
The upward trend of drug abuse among young people has been
reversed in the past two years, Lo said.
</P>
<P>
She said more people were aware of the negative effects of
drugs because of high-profile preventive education and publicity,
with expenditure increasing from three million HK dollars (384,615
 U.S. dollars) last year to four million HK dollars (512,820
U.S. dollars) this year.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
