<HEADLINE> Suspected Filipino Drug Boss Arrested in Hong Kong </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- A suspected Filipino drug
chief faces extradition after being arrested in Hong Kong, the
South China Morning Post reported today.
</P>
<P>
Filipino-Chinese businessman Alfred Tiongco, 47, was arrested
yesterday in a hotel in Tsim Sha Tsui, Kowloon, where he had been
staying since his arrival here on Sunday, the English language
newspaper said.
</P>
<P>
The arrest was made after a request from Manila on Monday, said
 Narcotics Bureau Superintendent Philip Cheng Po-yan.
</P>
<P>
Philippine Justice Department spokesman Jimmy Vicente said an
arrest warrant for illegal possession of a firearm had been issued
 while drug-related charges were finalized.
</P>
<P>
Extradition procedures will start Thursday in Eastern Court of
Hong Kong and police said that if they were successful, it would
be the first extradition between Hong Kong and the
Philippines. 
</P>
</TEXT>
