<HEADLINE> Better Navigation Services For East China Sea </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- More precise navigation
services are now possible for ships plying the East China Sea
waters, according to China's State Bureau of Surveying and Mapping.
</P>
<P>
Five radio navigation stations along the east China coast, at
Dalian, Qinhuangdao, Tianjin, Qingdao, and Shanghai, have been
using the global positioning system for navigation information on
a 300-sq.km. marine area since July 21.
</P>
<P>
The Ministry of Communications plans to build 22 similar radio
navigation stations along China's coast by the year 2000 to
provide more precise navigation information for ships in China's
waters.
</P>
<P>
The five stations already in operation were completed in
1996. The additional stations will better meet the navigation
needs of shipping, fishing, surveying and mapping, oil
exploration, and other marine projects. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0242 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Roundup: HK's Banking Business in Steady Growth </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Hong Kong's status as an
international financial center has been increasingly strengthened
in recent years with its banking business maintaining robust
growth.
</P>
<P>
Local banking business has turned on a fast growing track
since the 1970s due to its fine geographic location, improved
infrastructural facilities, highly-opening and low tax-rate
policies, and talented staff.
</P>
<P>
It has benefited a lot from the reforms and opening up in
China's interior areas since the 1980s.
</P>
<P>
Of the 100 largest banks in the world, 87 have branches in Hong
Kong.
</P>
<P>
According to the Census and Statistics Department of the Hong
Kong Special Administrative Region (SAR), the total assets of the
banking businesses in Hong Kong reached 8,699.2 billion HK
dollars (115.28 billion U.S. dollars) at the end of June this
year, an increase of 11.6 percent over the same period in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, the savings and deposits in the banking businesses
reached 4,260.5 billion HK dollars (546.21 billion U.S. dollars),
rising 14.6 percent and the credits and loans came to 1,599.5
billion HK dollars (205.06 billion U.S. dollars), increasing by
26.2 percent over the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The interim results of some banks listed in the Hong Kong Stock
Exchange showed that the growth of the average net profits of the
banks in the first half of the year increased by 27.3 percent,
with the Hongkong Shanghai Banking Corporation's profits rising 19
percent to 22.2 billion HK dollars (2.85 billion U.S. dollars) and
Kawah Bank Ltd. rising 50.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
The steady growth of Hong Kong's banking businesses is based on
a solid operation mechanism which agrees with the international
standard and practice.
</P>
<P>
On the other hand, banks in Hong Kong enjoyed sufficient
capital and circulating capital, which far exceed the ratio placed
by the banking supervision requirement.
</P>
<P>
The supervision mechanism over Hong Kong's banking businesses
has been greatly improved. While enhancing its supervision role,
the Hong Kong Monetary Authority formulated Banking Ordinance and
Guideline for Risk Management of Derivatives and Related Trading
Instruments to strictly define the requirements on bank
registration, control over credit and loans and investment as well
as the management of derivatives and other risk trading.
</P>
<P>
With the Annual Meetings of the World Bank Group and the
International Monetary Fund due to be held in Hong Kong, local
people are confident of the bright prospect of the banking
business in the Hong Kong SAR in the years to come.  
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
