<HEADLINE> EU Offers Nepal Preference for Garments Export </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KATHMANDU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The European Union (EU) has
exempted Nepal from the provisions of the rules of origin for
exporting ready-made garments to the EU countries, Nepali
newspapers reported today.
</P>
<P>
This arrangement will promote the exports of ready-made
garments, which are Nepal's major foreign exchange earner along
with the tourism and carpet industries.
</P>
<P>
Nepal had had to pay customs duties if its exports of
ready-made garments did not conform to the provisions in the rules
of origin as specified by the EU, the reports quoted the Nepali
Commerce Ministry as saying.
</P>
<P>
The Nepali government asked the EU to exempt Nepal from the
rules and the EU decided on September 3 to provide facility under
the general preference system to Nepal for exporting ready-made
garments as per the specified quantity, the reports said.
</P>
</TEXT>
