<HEADLINE> Six-Month Tourist Arrivals Up 1.53 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign tourist arrivals in
Thailand numbered 3.58 million during the first half of this year,
up 1.53 percent from the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Most of the tourists, about 2.27 million, came from East Asia
during January-June this year, up 1.6 percent, according to
statistics by the Thai Immigration Bureau and the Police
Department.
</P>
<P>
Tourists from Europe numbered 802,922, an increase of only 0.6
percent, while tourists from America totaled 202,359, up 7.75
percent.
</P>
<P>
However, tourists from South Asia dropped 12.4 percent during
the six months.
</P>
<P>
Thailand has set a target to attract 7.4 million tourists for
this year and the Tourism Authority of Thailand (TAT) is worried
that the number of visitors this year will fall below the target.
</P>
<P>
Local newspapers quoted the TAT as saying that cheating of
tourists remained the biggest problem spoiling the country's
tourism, while little progress had been made in attracting wealthy
tourists instead of the mass market.  
</P>
</TEXT>
