<HEADLINE> Auto Sales in Thailand Drop in First Eight Months </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BANGKOK, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Sales of vehicles posted
308,291 units in Thailand in the first eight months of this year,
falling 19.5 percent compared with the same period of last year.
</P>
<P>
Toyota still dominated the market, selling 92,041 vehicles
during the eight months, but down 12.3 percent from the same
period of last year, according to the latest statistics released
by Toyota Motor Thailand Co.
</P>
<P>
Sales of Isuzu vehicles ranked second, numbering 69,350 units,
down 14.3 percent, followed by Nissan with 37,355 units sold, down
41.8 percent.
</P>
<P>
Toyota claimed the largest share of 29.9 percent in the local
auto sales, followed by Isuzu with 22.5 percent and Nissan with
12.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
From January to August this year, cars sold in Thailand
numbered 111,990 units, down 0.7 percent compared with the same
period of last year. In August alone, car sales fell by 21.4
percent, the company said.
</P>
<P>
Toyota still led in car sales on the market in the first eight
months of this year, selling 41,161 units, followed by Honda with
29,270 units sold and Nissan with 9,569 units.
</P>
<P>
Sales of one-ton pickups fell by 24.9 percent to 159,921 units,
with Isuzu ranking first with 59,946 units sold, followed by
Toyota with 44,281 units sold and Nissan with 24,774 sold.
</P>
</TEXT>
