<HEADLINE> Albanians Celebrate Anniversary of Peza Conference </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
TIRANA, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Albanians held a rally today
in front of the historical Peza Conference monument, which is
located in Peza village near the capital city of Tirana.
</P>
<P>
The rally was a memorial to the 55th anniversary of a historic
meeting that occurred here during World War II.
</P>
<P>
On September 16, 1942, the Communist Party of Albania sponsored
a meeting in Peza. The meeting was attended by anti-Fascism
parties from a broad social base. Those who met here decided to
form a anti-Fascism national liberation front and to mobilize all
the Albanians in the fight against Nazi fascism.
</P>
<P>
The meeting was considered a milestone in the country's
struggle for national liberation and was of great significance in
its anti-Fascism drive.
</P>
<P>
President Rexhep Mejdani, government officials and thousands of
veterans attended the memorial event.
</P>
<P>
An article, carried by the Voice of People -- the mouthpiece of
the Socialist Party -- called on the Albanian people to "enhance
the meeting's spirit of national reconciliation and unity and to
make more efforts to build a prosperous country." 
</P>
</TEXT>
