<HEADLINE> One More S. Korean Bank Opens Office in Myanmar </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
YANGON, September 17 (Xinhua) -- One more South Korean bank --
Hana Bank -- has opened its representative office in Myanmar, the
official newspaper the New Light of Myanmar reported today.
</P>
<P>
Hana Bank, which began operations Tuesday, is the third South
Korean bank to open an office in the country after Korea Exchange
Bank and First Korea Bank.
</P>
<P>
Since Myanmar reformed its financial management system in line
with the market-oriented economy introduced in the late 1980s, it
has allowed the private sector to operate banking business while
permitting foreign banks to open representative offices in the
country.
</P>
<P>
So far, a total of 45 foreign banks from 16 countries or
regions have opened offices in Myanmar. Most of them are from
Japan, Thailand, France, Singapore and Malaysia.
</P>
<P>
Some of the foreign banks also plan to set up joint venture
banks in the country following Myanmar's entry into the second
phase of its financial reform.
</P>
<P>
According to official statistics, there are 25 private banks in
Myanmar in addition to six state-owned banks and some
state-private ones.  
</P>
</TEXT>
