<HEADLINE> Scenery In Confucius' Hometown Attracting Tourists </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
JINAN, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Qufu, the hometown of
Confucius, has made orchards, forests and farmland available to
tourists to see the beauty of the rural scenery around his
residence, temple and mausoleum.
</P>
<P>
Qufu, in Shandong province, is one of China's famous historical
and cultural cities, with 110 sites of historical interest. It has
over two million tourists a year.
</P>
<P>
To cater to different tastes, the city has decided to offer
special tourist programs to show some typical rural scenery of
northern China.
</P>
<P>
Tourists have a chance to stop between different attractions to
photograph orchards, pick fruit, or go boating and fishing.
</P>
<P>
Agricultural tourism now provides 30 percent of the city's
tourism income, and typical stays have gone from one or two days
to three or four. 
</P>
</TEXT>
