<HEADLINE> Dominican Republic, Guatemala Taste First Victories </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Dominican Republic
and Costa Rica snatched victories at the North and Central
American and Caribbean Volleyball Championships Tuesday, but both
teams were no closer to reaching next year's World Cup in Japan.
</P>
<P>
Dominican Republic beat Guatemala 17-15, 15-3, 15-5, as the
latter never won a single game in four straight matches. And it
was the first win for the Dominican men's team in the regional
tournament.
</P>
<P>
The victory smoothed the Dominicans' pain after a loss to
Barbados Sunday which cost the team its chance at a medal.
</P>
<P>
In the women's games, Costa Rica breezed past Trinidad and
Tobago 15-0, 15-6, 15-5 for its first win of the tournament.
