<HEADLINE> Portugal, Romania to Strengthen Cooperation </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUCHAREST, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Portugal will continue to
support Romania in its efforts to join the North Atlantic Treaty
Organization (NATO) and the European Union (EU).
</P>
<P>
Portuguese Prime Minister Antonio Guterres, who is on an
official visit to Romania, made the comment at a press conference
today after meeting his Romanian counterpart Victor Ciorbea.
</P>
<P>
During their talks, the two ministers exchanged views on the
current international situation and briefed each other on internal
affairs and foreign policy.
</P>
<P>
Ciorbea said the visit by Guterres was of great importance and
would help promote contacts on economy, trade, military and
culture between the two countries. He also hoped for more
investment from Portugal.
</P>
<P>
After the meeting, the two ministers signed cooperative
agreements on education, culture, sports, tourism and an agreement
on avoiding double taxation.
</P>
<P>
Guterres arrived here on Sunday. This is his first visit to
Romania since 1989. During his visit, he also met Romanian
President Emil Constantinescu and several members of the Romanian
parliament. 
