<HEADLINE> More Students In Beijing's Vacational Schools </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Children in Beijing have a
greater possibility of choosing a vacational school nowadays
instead of going the old route.
</P>
<P>
The city now has 459 secondary vacational schools, with 230,000
students, or 66 percent of the total number of high-school-age
students. There are 15,000 full-time teachers at these schools,
teaching 190 different courses.
</P>
<P>
Over the past few years, secondary vacational schools have
provided more than 600,000 trained personnel for the city's
economic development.
</P>
<P>
Enterprises and institutions have joined the government in
opening up new vacational schools, and in improving the quality of
those schools.
</P>
<P>
The city has also opened 29 vacational high schools, with a
total of 4,500 students.  
</P>
</TEXT>
