<HEADLINE> Hunan Trains Personnel for Foreign-Funded Businesses </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Foreign-funded businesses
have praised the efforts of Central China's Hunan Province to
train Chinese management personnel for local operations.
</P>
<P>
In 1994, foreign investors complained that some senior Chinese
managers knew little about management and were in dire need of
special training and education.
</P>
<P>
The province responded by establishing an education and
training center to train management personnel for foreign-funded
enterprises
</P>
<P>
The center has trained over 1,500 managers, accountants and key
management personnel for nearly 800 foreign-funded firms over the
past two years, according to Director Hu Xiangrong of the center.
</P>
<P>
The center has also established contacts with local colleges in
order to offer more opportunities for trainees to continue their
advanced studies in various areas, including MBA programs. Some
100 Chinese and foreign experts have been hired as part-time
teachers.
</P>
<P>
Training focuses on modern enterprise system, joint venture
management, accounting, foreign exchange administration, tariff
and real estate policies.
</P>
<P>
Wang Haobo, general manager of the Chenzhou Light &AMP; Carbon
Products Co. Ltd, said he learned few management concept in his
machinery major, but that two years of training provided by the
center has helped promote and elevate his business to a position
as a local model. 
</P>
</TEXT>
