<HEADLINE> Bus Accident Kills 10 in Venezuela </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CARACAS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Ten people were killed and 35
others injured after a passenger bus turned over in Portuguesa
State, central west Venezuela, police said today.
</P>
<P>
The accident occurred Monday on the General Jose Antonio Paez
highway in Araure, 325 kilometers west of the capital.
</P>
<P>
The bus was traveling at an excessive rate speed and overturned
on a curve when a horse attempted to cross the highway. The driver
was unable to stop the vehicle in time to keep from hitting the
animal, swerved and ran off the road.
</P>
<P>
The bus's roof reportedly was torn off in the crash. 
