<HEADLINE> Panama Authorizes U.S. Military Exercises </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
PANAMA CITY, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The Panamanian government
has authorized the U.S. army to perform military exercises off the
Canal`s coasts, a foreign ministry spokesman said today.
</P>
<P>
"The military exercise will include the deployment of
specialized troops, logistic people to supply fuel and the use of
conventional weapons, as well as two MH-60 helicopters," the
spokesman said.
</P>
<P>
The operations will take place on September 27. The objective
of the exercise is to enhance cooperation and coordinate the
participation of U.S. armed forces in the defense and security of
the Panama Canal, he said.
</P>
<P>
Panama and the United States signed a neutrality accord
included in the 1977 Torrijos-Carter Treaties, which committed the
U.S. Army to guarantee the integrity and security of the canal
after it is returned to Panama in 1999.
</P>
<P>
"According to treaties regarding the Canal, U.S. military
troops must leave Panama before midday of December 31 1999," the
spokesman added. 
</P>
