<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China's Largest Private Enterprise </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHENGDU, September 17 (Xinhua) -- The Hope Group, a major feed
producer in southwest China's Sichuan Province, recently emerged
as China's leading private enterprise after doubling its output
and sales volumes on an almost annual basis since 1992.
</P>
<P>
The group, established in 1982 with an investment of 1,000
yuan, recorded a 1992 output value of 300 million yuan, with the
figure rising to 800 million yuan in 1993, 1.7 billion yuan in
1994, 3.5 billion yuan in 1995 and 5 billion yuan in 1996.
</P>
<P>
Hope increased its total feed production in the first half of
this year by 80 percent on a year-on-year basis, with the
production value for the period doubling that of the 1996 period,
reaching five billion yuan.
</P>
<P>
The group has 89 subsidiaries engaged in feed processing
nationwide and has in recent years established feed mills in a
number of Southeast Asian nations.
</P>
<P>
Hope President Liu Yonghao said the group's feed production
capacity will hit 10 million tons annually by early next
century. 
</P>
</TEXT>
