<HEADLINE> Italy to Bid for 2006 Winter Olympics </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ROME, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Italy's Veneto, one of 20
regions in the country, has formally decided on Tuesday to bid for
the hosting of the 2006 Winter Olympic Games.
</P>
<P>
The regional authorities passed a resolution on Tuesday,
allocating three billion liras (some 1.7 million U.S. dollars) for
the bidding process.
</P>
<P>
The Italians considered that Veneto region boasts of three
advantages in its Olympic bid as the infrastructure is already in
place, the enviromental conditions will not be in danger and a
rich heritage of historical, artistic and cultural relics.
</P>
<P>
Veneto is estimated to spend 12 billion liras in its bidding
efforts and the regional government was alreay busy in seeking
private sectors for their financial support.
</P>
<P>
The Veneto region is located in the Northeastern part of Italy
with natural skiing facilities in Dolomiti mountains.
</P>
<P>
In July, Italy, Slovenia and Austria had suggested for a joint
bid for the Winter Olympics. 
</P>
</TEXT>
