<HEADLINE> Revenues From Fishing Exports Rise in Chile </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SANTIAGO, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Fishing exports in Chile
earned 1.15 billion U.S. dollars during the first eight months of
this year, a 4.8 percent increase over the same period last year.
an official report said today.
</P>
<P>
The increase is attributed to the price hike in the sales of
sea products, though the amount of fish caught fell from 5.14
million tons in the first eight months of 1996 to 4.45 million
tons in the same period this year.
</P>
<P>
Chile has exported fish products to 125 countries, with 40
percent of the total going to Japan, the report said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
