<HEADLINE> U.S. Runner Slaney Cleared of Doping Charges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Suspended American runner
Mary Slaney committed no doping offense last year and was
permitted to run again, the USA Track &AMP; Field said on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The U.S. governing body for athletics said a doping hearing
board had cleared Slaney following a weekend hearing in Chicago.
</P>
<P>
The International Amateur Athletic Federation (IAAF) suspended
Slaney in June for her drug test at the 1996 U.S. Olympic trials.
</P>
<P>
The test found Slaney to have a higher ratio of testosterone to
epitestosterone although she denied taking steroids or any drugs
banned by the IAAF. 
</P>
</TEXT>
