<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0322 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Getting Lease On Life In Central China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CHANGSHA, September 17 (Xinhua) -- Residents in the capital of
central China's Hunan Province are finding many more things that
can be leased, like cars, computers and telephones.
</P>
<P>
At the Weiyi Company, the city's largest car leaser, 5,000 yuan
as a surety and photocopies of an ID card and driver's license
will get you a rental car. Daily rates run from 420 yuan for a
Santana to 2,000 yuan for a Mercedes-Benz.
</P>
<P>
The company is doing a steady business, earning more than
100,000 yuan each month on average in the three years it has been
in operation.
</P>
<P>
Business people in town for a deal often complain of
inconvenient communications. To meet their needs, the local
telecommunications office started a phone leasing
service. Customers put a 500-yuan deposit and pay 300 yuan.
</P>
<P>
And, with the increasing popularity of computers, computer
leasing has become another good business in the city. Monthly
rates are slightly over 100 yuan. According to one employee, 60
percent of the customers are high school students. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
