<BODY>
<HEADLINE> French Clubs Kick Off Perfectly in UEFA Cup </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, September 16 (Xinhua) -- All seven French clubs either
won or draw their openers to boost their morale in the UEFA Cup
first-leg first-round matches on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Auxerre won the away game against Deportivo La Coruna of Spain
2-1, Metz scored a 2-0 win away to Belgian Mouscron while Nantes
forced a 2-2 draw away against Denmark's Aarhus.
</P>
<P>
Among those played at home, Bastia toppled Portuguese Benfica
1-0, Lyon stunned Brondy of Denmark 4-1, Bordeaux forced to a
scoreless draw with England giants Aston Villa, while Strasbourg
defeated Glasgow Rangers of Scotland 2-1 with all the goals from
the penalty spot.
</P>
<P>
Yet, the Italian clubs had mixed fortunes. Inter Milan snatched
a 2-0 home victory over Swiss Neuchatel and Lazio scored all the
four goals in the second half to beat home squad Vitoria Guimaraes
of Portugal 4-0, but Udinese was beat 1-0 in Poland by Widzew Lodz
and Sampdoria stumbled over Athletic Bilbao 2-1.
</P>
<P>
British clubs were eager to forget the night. Apart from Aston
Villa and Rangers, both lost the openers, Arsenal also went down
1-0 in Greece to PAOK Salonika, and Leicester City was beated by
Atletico of Spain 2-1.
</P>
<P>
Liverpool also suffered a miserable fate as they drew with
Celtic 2-2 in Glasgow.
</P>
<P>
Among other matches, 1860 Munich of Germany won 1-0 over Pori
in Finland, Dutch giants Ajax struggled for a 1-1 draw away to
Maribor Teatanic in Slovenia, and Turkey's Trabzonspor beat German
Bochum 2-0.
</P>
<P>
The biggest score of the night came from Zagreb, where Croatia
Zagreb were held 4-4 by Switzerland's Grasshopper Zurich, and
Austrian Salzburg scored a thrilling win 4-3 over Anderlecht of
Belgium.
</P>
<P>
Auxerre's win was sealed by two second half late goals through
Bernard Diomede and Stephane Guivarch, while two first-half goals
from Frederic Meyrieu and Bruno Rodriguez gave Metz a 2-0 win at
Mouscron.
</P>
<P>
Brazilian internationals came to rescue Inter Milan as both
Ronaldo and Ze Elias scored the second half goals to put the
Italian club for a 2-0 win over Neuchatel.
</P>
<P>
Ronaldo scored in the 58th minute, his second in as many games
for his new club after his transfer from Barcelona.
</P>
<P>
Polish champions Widzew Lodz defeated Udinese 1-0 as defender
Daniel Bogusz drove home the second half winner, after an arguable
penalty kick for Oliver Bierhoff was denied and the Brazilian was
booked for "faking" in the box.
</P>
<P>
Another Brazilian star Juninho scored the equaliser to put
Atletico Madrid for a 2-1 win over Leicester City before Christian
Vieri converted from the spot to give the Spaniards victory.
</P>
<P>
Greek Salonika defeated England Premiership giants Arsenal 1-0
through midfielder Konstantinos Fratzescos who scored the decisive
goal on the hour.
</P>
<P>
Arsenal that suffered the absence of Dennis Bergkamp, produced
only one real chance throughout the game which was sqaundered by
Ian Wright, one of three Arsenal players booked. 
</P>
</TEXT>
