<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0327 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Oscar De Rojas of Venezuela Elected Chairman of </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Oscar R. de Rojas, the
deputy representative of Venezuela to the United Nations, was
today elected chairman of the Second Committee (Economic and
Financial) of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
From 1991 to 1995, de Rojas served as permanent observer to the
U.N. for the Latin American Economic System (SELA).
</P>
<P>
Prior to that he was director-general for international
economics affairs in his countrty's Foreign Ministry (1989-1991),
Venezuela's deputy permanent representative to the U.N. Office in
Geneva (1987-1989), and head of the Economic Section at its
mission to the U.N. in New York.
</P>
<P>
From 1980 to 1983, de Rojas was director-general for
international technical cooperation in the National Office of
Coordination and Planning, where he had served years earlier as an
economic development analyst in its Macroeconomic Programing
Division (1972-1973).
</P>
<P>
De Rojas has participated extensively in international
economic meetings and conferences since 1974, when he became
executive assistant to the minister of state for international
economic affairs (1974-1977).
</P>
<P>
De Rojas, 50, earned a Bachelor of Science degree in
engineering from Louisiana State University in 1968. At Columbia
University he earned a Master of Arts degree in economics in 1971
and a Master of International Affairs degree in 1972. 
</P>
</TEXT>
