<DOCNO> XIE19970917.0332 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1997-09-17 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Udovenko: UN Remains Unique for Addressing New Challenges </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- The United Nations was
the unique and indispensable mechanism for addressing new
challenges, Hennadiy Udovenko, president of the 52nd session of
the General Assembly, stressed today.
</P>
<P>
Speaking after elected as the president of the 52nd session of
the General Assembly, Udovenko said, "Peace and security are now
more threatened by the internal civil and ethnic strife,
international terrorism and proliferation of nuclear arms and
materials. These threats will not automatically disappear, and
they will, therefore, require the priority attention on the part
of the United Nations."
</P>
<P>
"The United Nations remains the unique and dispensable
mechanism for addressing new challenges, and resolution of
problems related to the maintenance of international peace and
security, promotion of sustained economic growth and sustainable
development, human rights, justice and international law," said
the president.
</P>
<P>
On strengthening the role of the organization, Udovenko said
the principles should be efficiency, transparency, democratization of
the decision-making process, realism and responsibility.
</P>
<P>
He said assuring the United Nations financial viability was
an essential condition for the success of its reform. To solve
the financial problem, political will and cooperative approach
should be strengthened, he added. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
