<HEADLINE> Chowdhury of Bangladesh Elected Chairman of UN </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
UNITED NATIONS, September 16 (Xinhua) -- Anwarul Karim
Chowdhury of Bangladesh was elected today chairman of the Fifth
Committee (Administrative and Budgetary) of the 52nd Session of
the General Assembly of the United Nations.
</P>
<P>
The elections were held at the opening ceremony of the U.N.
session. The Fifth Committee is one of the six committees under
the U.N. General Assembly.
</P>
<P>
Chowdhury has served as the permanent representative of
Bangladesh to the United Nations since September 1996.
</P>
<P>
Since then, he served as vice-president of the Economic and
Social Council and led his country's delegation to the council's
substantive session in Geneva last July.
</P>
<P>
Before his appointment as permanent representative, Chowdhury
was secretary of the Executive Board of the United Nations
Children's Fund (UNICEF) in New York and UNICEf director for
Japan, Australia and New Zealand.
</P>
<P>
The new chairman represented Bangladesh at 14 regular General
Assembly sessions. During his career, he has specialized in
development issues and has been closely involved in international
economic and social issues, representing his country at various
forums.
</P>
<P>
A holder of a Master degree, with honors, in contemporary
history, from the University of Dhaka, Chowdhury is a regular
contributor to journals on development issues. 
